text.tspan: Ratio of female to male labor force participation rates
Shown is the female-to-male ratio of labor force participation rates, calculated by dividing the labor force participation
rate among women, by the corresponding rate for men. The labor force participation rate is defined as the proportion
of the population ages 15+ that is economically active.
